The paper deals with predicting the time evolution of influence on a propagation network, which is a problem related to social influence and information diffusion. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). The paper also involves differential equations and probability mass functions, which are related to mathematical modeling and analysis, suggesting the sub-category cs.SD (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses the computational challenges of the problem and proposes scalable algorithms, which are related to machine learning and optimization, suggesting the sub-category cs.SY (Machine Learning). The paper also deals with network topology and activation rates, which are related to network science and graph theory, suggesting the sub-category cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper involves predicting the expected number of activated nodes, which is related to network influence and diffusion, suggesting the sub-category cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture).
